low plastic board across the surface toward and past the blade, demonstrating a pretend sawing motion. The board slides steadily from right to left, while another yellow block sits farther back on the bench.\n\nNear the end, the child’s face fills the scene in warm light, looking downward at a small yellow plastic piece held in both hands. Large white “Fisher-Price” text appears across the lower part of the screen. The child brings the piece closer, studies it, then begins to smile subtly, still focused on the toy. The final images hold on the child’s pleased expression and hands working with the yellow piece, with the Fisher-Price name remaining visible at the bottom.",
